# Canvas frame animations

Every Figma canvas frame in `components/frame/` must include scroll-triggered entrance animations. Do not wait for the user to ask.

## Required pattern

1. Mark the frame root as a client component when needed (`"use client"`).
2. Use `useFrameInView` from `@/components/frame/use-frame-in-view`.
3. Apply classes: `frame-animated` and `frame-in-view` when visible.
4. Tag animatable blocks with `data-frame-reveal` using semantic names.

```tsx
"use client";

import { useFrameInView } from "@/components/frame/use-frame-in-view";

export default function MyFrame() {
  const { ref, inView } = useFrameInView(0.15);

  return (
    <section
      ref={ref}
      className={`frame-animated ${inView ? "frame-in-view" : ""} ...`}
    >
      <div data-frame-reveal="badge">...</div>
      <h2 data-frame-reveal="title">...</h2>
      <p data-frame-reveal="description">...</p>
      <div data-frame-reveal="actions">...</div>
      <div data-frame-reveal="media">...</div>
    </section>
  );
}
```

## Reveal tokens (defined in `app/globals.css`)

| Token | Use for |
|-------|---------|
| `badge` | Status / award pills |
| `title` | Main heading |
| `description` | Body copy |
| `tech` | Tech stack line |
| `actions` | Buttons / CTAs |
| `media` | Photos, screenshots (slides in from right) |
| `terminal` | Terminal or secondary panel |
| `tech-grid` | Icon grids |
| `employers` | Logo / employer rows |
| `logo` | Project logo (right column) |
| `carousel` | Image carousel strip |
| `arrow` | Carousel nav control |

Optional: `data-frame-dot` on status dots, `.frame-float` on logos after entrance.

## Rules

- CSS-only animations in `globals.css` — no animation libraries unless explicitly requested.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` (already handled globally).
- Interactive elements (`a`, `button`) must remain clickable inside the pannable canvas.
- Add hover/active micro-interactions on buttons (`hover:scale-[1.03]`, `active:scale-[0.98]`).
- Stagger top-to-bottom, left column before right column.
